Former champions, Niger United of Minna defeated Confluence Stars 37-28 to continue their winning streak in the on-going Prudent Energy Handball Premier League at Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja. The high tempo game was keenly contested in the early stages but Niger United were dominant towards the end of the first half. At the resumption of the second half, the Minna side took over the game fully and won the game to the admiration of the fans. In the other men’s category games , Benue Buffaloes lost to Kano Pillars 24–37, while Police Machine inflicted the third defeat on Owena Kings. The game ended 26–21.   Zenith Bank tennis grand slam enters crucial stages     Over N60m jackpot for 8th Okpekpe Road Race     INTERNATIONAL FRIENDLIES: Moffi, Bonke, Adeleye get late…   In the women’s category, Defender Babes lost to Safety Babes 22-31, Imo Grasshoppers and Rima Queens ended 37–37 draw while Seasider Queens walk over Kada Queens. Coach Ronke Saliu of Owena Kings expressed disappointment over the three defeats her team has suffered but noted that she is hopeful that the players will do better in subsequent games. She said: “It really demoralizing to see my team lose three games in a row. We always give our best in all our games but results have not gone our way. “ I am hopeful that we will win some games as the league progresses. The teams would have been stronger if we were able to sign some of the players that trained with us before the league began.”